text: Lo Yueh-ying (born 7 January 1970) is a Taiwanese taekwondo athlete. She won at the 1988 Summer Olympics, where taekwondo was a demonstration sport, in the finweight event. At the Asian Taekwondo Championships she became Asian champion in 1994 after winning the silver medal in 1992. == References == Category:1970 births Category:Taekwondo practitioners Category:Taiwanese sportspeople Category:Living people
